node.text:
You can make these buns for lunch or dinner, your faily will love them! 

INGREDIENTS
Dough:
½ kg flour
1 tbsp milk powder
4 tbsp vegetable oil
1 tsp salt
1 tsp sugar
7g dry yeast
Water
Egg
Sesame seeds
 
Filling:
2 red onions
2 bell peppers
Salt
Pepper
Garlic powder
Minced meat
Cheese

METHOD
Pour yeast and sugar into a glass of warm water and mix.
Add milk powder and salt to a bowl with flour and mix. Add the oil and the yeast-sugar mixture and mix again.
Keep mixing until you get a dough.
Place in a bowl, cover with cling film and let it rest until it is doubled in size. Cook pepper and chopped onion in a pan. Add salt, pepper, oil, garlic powder.
Add ground beef to one side of the pan, add more salt, pepper, garlic powder, and cook. Mix everything and continue cooking.
Divide the dough in two. Flatten each ball into a square. Draw several squares in the dough and add a little of the minced meat mixture into each square.
Add grated cheese to each square. Brush some water on the edges of the square.
Cover the entire square with the other piece of dough. Use your fingers to finish forming the squares and cut.
Place each square on a baking sheet. Brush beat egg on each one and sprinkle with sesame seeds.
Bake for 20 minutes at 180ºC (356ºF).

You won't be able to stop at one!

INGREDIENTS
150g (2/3 cup) butter
400g (3 1/4 cups) flour
100ml (1/2 cup) milk
1 tbsp vanilla extract
50g (1/2 cup) powdered sugar
1 egg
1/3 tsp salt

150g chocolate
500ml (2 1/4 cups) milk
70g (1/3 cup) sugar
50g (1/4 cup) butter
40g (1/3 cup) starch
1 egg
Sugar
Raspberries for decoration

METHOD
In a bowl mix together flour, sugar, and butter. Add in milk and egg.
In a pan add milk, cornstarch, and sugar, cook on low heat until thick. Turn off the heat and add in chocolate, butter, and vanilla extract.
Divide the dough into two pieces. Roll out each piece and cut it into strips. Wind each strip on a cone.
Transfer to the baking pan and spread with egg and sprinkle with sugar, bake at 180’C (350’F) for 30 minutes.
Fill each cone with prepared chocolate cream.

INGREDIENTS
Cookies box
Silicon
Rope
Chopsticks

METHOD
Line the inside of an empty cookie box with string.
Cut the chopsticks into smaller pieces and cover them with string. Use the sticks to make two handles and glue them to the outside of the box.
Cover the outside of the box with thick rope. Use to store fruit.

A no-fail recipe to make great and delicious bread at home! 
 
INGREDIENTS
30ml (4 tbsp) olive oil
7g dry yeast
1 tsp salt
340ml (1 1/2 cups) water
600g (5 cups) flour

METHOD
In a bowl mix together warm water with yeast, oil, flour and salt. Let the dough rise for about 2 hours (or until double).
Divide into three pieces and roll out them, then roll up in the shape of a baguette.
Transfer to the baking pan and let them rise for 1 hour more.
Make the cuts and sprinkle with flour.
Bake at 200 ‘C ( 390’F) for 20 minutes.

These #fritters are so creamy that you will forget your usual pancakes!

INGREDIENTS
250g (1 cup) cottage cheese
10g (2 tsp) vanilla sugar
50g (¼ cup) sugar
180ml (¾ cup) milk
25ml (2 tbsp) oil
2 eggs
150g (1 1/5 cups) flour
5g (1 tsp) baking powder
Apricot jam

METHOD
Add cheese, milk, egg yolks, sugar, vanilla sugar, oil to a mixing bowl. Whisk the mixture. Add flour and baking powder. Stir.
Whisk the egg whites and salt with a mixer and mix with the previous mixture.
Fry in an oiled pan.
Fill with jam. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve.

220ml (1 cup) yogurt
150g (1 1/4 cup) flour
1 egg
1 tbsp sugar
1 tsp soda
1/2 tsp salt
200g minced meat
1/2 tsp salt
1/3 tsp pepper
2 tbsp shredded parmesan

METHOD
In a bowl mix together yogurt, egg and spices, add in flour.
In another bowl mix together meat with salt, pepper and Parmesan.
Into the pan on medium heat add a tablespoon of prepared mixture top it with meat and another tablespoon of the mixture.
Fry from both sides.

This method is genius! 😍😍

INGREDIENTS
 300g (2 cups) all-purpose flour;
 60g (¼ cup) butter, melted;
 100ml (⅓ cup+2 tbsp) water;
 Cornstarch.
 
METHOD
 Combine water, melted butter and flour to form a smooth dough.

This method to cook eggs is genius! You've never seen anything like this!

INGREDIENTS
250g (2 cups) flour
1 tsp salt
120ml (2/3 cup) water
4 tbsp oil
100 g melted butter
6 eggs

METHOD
In a bowl mix together water, oil, salt and flour. Let the dough rest for 30 minutes. Divide the dough into 6 pieces and roll out each.
Spread with melted butter and roll the dough. Roll out again for a little. Fry it in the pan on medium heat adding the egg into each bread.

Ever tried to fry pasta? You'll fall in love with this recipe! 
 
INGREDIENTS
Paccheri pasta
Ricotta
Cooked ham
Provolone
Parmesan
3 eggs
Breadcrumbs
Salt
Pepper
Oil

METHOD
Boil the pasta for 10 minutes and let it cool.
Mix ricotta, diced ham, cheese, salt, pepper, and parmesan in a bowl. Place the mixture in a piping bag.
Fill each piece of pasta with the mixture.
Beat 3 eggs, add salt, then dip the filled pasta in the egg and cover very well with bread crumbs. Coat twice.
Use a toothpick to check that the oil is hot and fry the pasta.

This is the most incredible way to fry an #eggplant!

INGREDIENTS
Eggplants
Salt
Water
Tapioca flour
Oil

METHOD
Peel an eggplant. Cut into large chunks.
Form a grid on each piece without cutting it all together.
Add salt to a bowl with water and place each piece of eggplant and wait for 20 minutes.
Cover each piece with flour. Deep fry with very hot oil.
Serve with sour cream.

A simple method to make amazing fluffy #bread!

INGREDIENTS
400ml (1 3/4 cup) Milk
7g dry yeast
2 tbsp sugar
600g (4 cups) Flour
1 tsp salt
30ml (2 1/4 tbsp) Oil
Butter
Apricot jam

METHOD
In a bowl mix together warm milk with sugar and yeast, add flour and salt. Let the dough rise for about 40 minutes.
Divide the dough into 8 pieces.
Boil in hot water for 3 minutes from both sides.
Transfer to the baking pan and bake for 20 minutes at 200’C(390’F).
Serve with butter and jam.

You can make these buns for lunch or dinner, your faily will love them! 

INGREDIENTS
Dough:
½ kg flour
1 tbsp milk powder
4 tbsp vegetable oil
1 tsp salt
1 tsp sugar
7g dry yeast
Water
Egg
Sesame seeds
 
Filling:
2 red onions
2 bell peppers
Salt
Pepper
Garlic powder
Minced meat
Cheese

METHOD
Pour yeast and sugar into a glass of warm water and mix.
Add milk powder and salt to a bowl with flour and mix. Add the oil and the yeast-sugar mixture and mix again.
Keep mixing until you get a dough.
Place in a bowl, cover with cling film and let it rest until it is doubled in size. Cook pepper and chopped onion in a pan. Add salt, pepper, oil, garlic powder.
Add ground beef to one side of the pan, add more salt, pepper, garlic powder, and cook. Mix everything and continue cooking.
Divide the dough in two. Flatten each ball into a square. Draw several squares in the dough and add a little of the minced meat mixture into each square.
Add grated cheese to each square. Brush some water on the edges of the square.
Cover the entire square with the other piece of dough. Use your fingers to finish forming the squares and cut.
Place each square on a baking sheet. Brush beat egg on each one and sprinkle with sesame seeds.
Bake for 20 minutes at 180ºC (356ºF).

INGREDIENTS
6-8 chicken legs
8-10 medium potatoes
1 tsp salt
1/2 tsp black pepper
1/2 tsp oregano
1/2 tsp rosemary
1 tbsp oil
1/2 tsp salt
1/2 tsp black pepper
1/2 tsp rosemary

METHOD
Sprinkle chicken legs with salt, pepper, oregano, and rosemary.
Put chicken legs into the baking pan.
Cut potatoes and mix with oil, salt, pepper, and rosemary.
Bake everything at 200°C (390°F) for 35-40 minutes.

You won't be able to stop at one!

INGREDIENTS
150g (2/3 cup) butter
400g (3 1/4 cups) flour
100ml (1/2 cup) milk
1 tbsp vanilla extract
50g (1/2 cup) powdered sugar
1 egg
1/3 tsp salt

150g chocolate
500ml (2 1/4 cups) milk
70g (1/3 cup) sugar
50g (1/4 cup) butter
40g (1/3 cup) starch
1 egg
Sugar
Raspberries for decoration

METHOD
In a bowl mix together flour, sugar, and butter. Add in milk and egg.
In a pan add milk, cornstarch, and sugar, cook on low heat until thick. Turn off the heat and add in chocolate, butter, and vanilla extract.
Divide the dough into two pieces. Roll out each piece and cut it into strips. Wind each strip on a cone.
Transfer to the baking pan and spread with egg and sprinkle with sugar, bake at 180’C (350’F) for 30 minutes.
Fill each cone with prepared chocolate cream.

A fun idea to turn a simple danish cookies box into something amazing!

INGREDIENTS
Cookies box
Silicon
Rope
Chopsticks

METHOD
Line the inside of an empty cookie box with string.
Cut the chopsticks into smaller pieces and cover them with string. Use the sticks to make two handles and glue them to the outside of the box.
Cover the outside of the box with thick rope. Use to store fruit.

A no-fail recipe to make great and delicious bread at home! 
 
INGREDIENTS
30ml (4 tbsp) olive oil
7g dry yeast
1 tsp salt
340ml (1 1/2 cups) water
600g (5 cups) flour

METHOD
In a bowl mix together warm water with yeast, oil, flour and salt. Let the dough rise for about 2 hours (or until double).
Divide into three pieces and roll out them, then roll up in the shape of a baguette.
Transfer to the baking pan and let them rise for 1 hour more.
Make the cuts and sprinkle with flour.
Bake at 200 ‘C ( 390’F) for 20 minutes.

Easy and tasty, these bacon #meatballs are perfect for a delicious dinner! 
 
INGREDIENTS
300g minced meat
40g (3 pieces) bread
100ml (1/2 cup) milk
40g onion
2g (1 tsp) coriander
Garlic
10g (2 1/2 tbsp) parsley
2 eggs
6g (1 tsp) salt
Pepper
200g bacon
Cheese

METHOD
In a small bowl add the bread and pour the milk on top. Chop the bread with a fork to soak the milk.
In another bowl add the meat, eggs, bread with milk, onion, garlic, parsley, coriander, salt, pepper and mix well with the hands.
Create the small balls with your hands, add a small piece of cheese inside and roll them into the slice of the bacon.
Transfer the meatloaves into the glass baking tray and bake at 356°F/180°C for 30 minutes.

Have you ever made #pesto at home? It's so delicious! 🌱

Its preparation is not easy because the doses of the ingredients, which must be high-quality ingredients, and the order in which they are mixed, must be respected. There are, therefore, guidelines that establish how the real pesto alla Genovese is prepared.

Wash the basil leaves under running water delicately, so as not to ruin them too much.

Dry them by tapping them with a clean cloth, without breaking the leaves.

Grate the pecorino and Parmesan cheese.

Put the basil leaves in the mortar a small bunch at a time and pound them using a circular motion so that the leaves gradually start breaking apart. Pound the garlic using the pestle and mortar, after that, add the coarse salt. 

Add the pine nuts and continue to pound to break them up into lots of small pieces

Combine the grated pecorino cheese and grated Parmesan cheese to the mixture and, finally, drizzle with olive oil to allow it to absorb all the scents.

Homemade pesto can be stored in a container, to keep it from turning black, and frozen. It can also be kept in the refrigerator for a couple of months.
